news.title: Greenply Industries' net profit up by 19% to Rs 29 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: The company's revenue during the October-December period of the 2021-22 fiscal was Rs 421.1 crore, up by over 23 per cent on a year-on-year (y-o-y) basis.

news.title: Asset quality issues to affect performance of real estate-focused non-banks till FY23: Report
news.para: ​The performance of non-banks (non-banking financial companies and housing finance companies) in recent years has been marred by several challenges as entities have grappled with fund-raising challenges and asset quality issues, domestic rating agency Icra Ratings said in a report on Monday.

news.title: Noida: No registry yet, Sports City homebuyers to move court
news.para: Like Vardhan, around 15,000 flats owners in nearly 15 projects in the sector are waiting to get their units registered in lieu of the pending Sports City project that was aimed at providing the best sporting infrastructure along with housing.

news.title: Interest of homebuyers gets priority over banks: SC
news.para: The government had amended the Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code making homebuyers part of the committee of creditors deciding the fate of the company but they had not been given precedence in payment of dues in case of liquidation.

news.title: NCDRC directs Supertech to refund the paid amount with interest to home buyers
news.para: The bench headed by Dr. SM Kantikar directed the Supertech to refund the entire paid-up amount along with interest at the rate of 9 per cent per annum within six weeks after which it will attract interest at the rate of 12 per cent per annum.

news.title: MahaRERA issues warrants for Rs 633 crore against errant builders
news.para: Mumbai suburban area led the pack with 302 such recoveries, followed by Pune (162) and Thane (99). The warrants were issued in relation to 256 projects, of which 83 are in Pune, followed by 63 in Mumbai suburban and 41 in Thane.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP official meets Chintels Paradiso residents
news.para: ​​Gurugram district town planner RS Bhath, who visited the society on Monday, held a marathon meeting with the residents and got the approval for a structural audit of the tower from IIT Delhi.

news.title: Jaypee Infratech posts Rs 540 crore loss in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 294.76 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 248.57 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: SC seeks ED's response on bail plea of jailed ex-CFO of Amrapali group
news.para: ​A bench comprising Justices U U Lalit, S Ravindra Bhat, and P S Narasimha took note of the submissions that Wadhwa has been ailing and needed medical attention and asked the probe agency to file the response in two weeks.

news.title: SC asks Centre to examine if state rules under RERA subserve interest of buyers
news.para: A bench of Justices D Y Chandrachud and Surya Kant gave three months to the Centre to examine if there are any deviations in the rules framed by the states to the rules framed by the Centre in 2016 and to place the report by first week of May, 2022.

news.title: Parsvnath Developers posts Rs 68.87 crore loss in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 301.44 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 73.42 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Omaxe posts Rs 38.56 crore loss in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income rose 75 per cent to Rs 184.26 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal from Rs 105.40 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Kohinoor Group buys 32 acre land in Pune for Rs 200 crore
news.para: Property consultant Anarock said it facilitated the deal between the two parties. The deal for 32 acres of prime land at Wagholi has been concluded.

news.title: As protests continue, Haryana CM orders structural audit of Chintels Paradiso
news.para: ​As residents of several other housing societies in New Gurugram expressed apprehensions about the safety of their buildings, Khattar also asked the local administration to identify all such buildings through the town and country planning department or the residents' welfare associations and get their audits done at the builders' expense.

news.title: Migsun takes over Parsvnath Palacia in Greater Noida
news.para: Spread over 9 acres, the 2 and 3 BHK apartments in 1320 sq ft to 1835 sq ft configurations. The project, with six towers and 442 units, provides a vast range of amenities including Cycling & Jogging Track, Gymnasium, Swimming Pool and Lift.
